BBQ Pork Macaroni
Makes 4 servings ~ 450 cal each
---------------------------------

Ingredients
-----------
8 oz smoked and shredded pork
8 oz large macaroni noodles
3/4 cup diced white onion
3/4 chopped broccoli
2 Tbsp extra virgin olive oil
3 Tbsp smoked chipotle pepper flakes
1 1/2 Tbsp fresh minced garlic
1/2 cup brown sugar barbeque sauce

Instructions
------------
1. If smoked pork isn't fresh off the smoker, reheat according to your preferred method
2. Prepare noodles to your desired tenderness
3. In a large wok, heat olive oil over medium heat
4. Add garlic and onion to wok and lightly sautee for 3 minutes
5. Add noodles, pork, broccoli and pepper while stirring
6. Continue stirring over medium heat for 2 minutes
7. Remove wok from heat (or turn off heat if electric wok) and stir in BBQ sauce
8. Serve and enjoy
